        "create_time": 1777135680.325,
        "update_time": null,
        "content": {
          "content_type": "text",
          "parts": [
            "Check the following quoted paragraph: \"Next, choose an appropriate tradeoff depending on task requirements and the context in which the visualization will be used. Richer et al.~\\cite{richer2022scalability} provide a model of scalability that treats computation time delay and representativeness as effort that depends on problem size, available resources, and assumptions about the deployment context. Extending on the scalability model, we recommend to identify a tradeoff empirically by measuring user task performance~\\cite{lam2011empirical}, such as task completion accuracy or time, across different analysis tasks.\"\n\nSuggest a wording alternate to \"Extending on the scalability model\", because I am not extending the model, I am just suggesting other than following the model."
          ]
        },
